Job description 36 : 
Lead and manage product or subsystem development projects from concept to production.
Drive innovation and technology development aligned with product roadmap and business strategy.
Collaborate with design, simulation, testing, manufacturing, and quality teams for design feasibility, prototyping, and validation.
Conduct benchmarking, reverse engineering, and technology scouting.
Oversee detailed design, tolerance stack-up, GD&T, and engineering documentation.
Analyze test data, lead design iterations, and approve final product release.
Ensure projects meet quality, cost, and timing (QCT) targets.
Support patent filings, technical dossiers, and regulatory submissions.
Train and mentor junior engineers in design tools, processes, and standards

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Job description 37 : 
Execute a variety of reliability tests for internal combustion engines, including Durability, Function, Strength, and Friction
Testing data analysis, result compilation, report preparation and presentations
Analysis and resolution of quality issues.
Execution of advance projects and studies for improving quality & reliability of engines.
Summarization of findings along with objective evaluation of counter-measure effectiveness.
Develop and implement improvements to testing processes and procedures
Working in dynamic team for coordination with Engine testing, vehicle testing, production, supply chain, quality etc


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Job description 38 : 
Software engineering, involving feature breakdown, task specification, programming, testing, documentation, source code management, deployment, and issue tracking.
Web-based HMI development using our design language.
Collaborating closely with our UX designers to enhance user experiences.
Establishing global automation standards for the platforms we use through cross-site collaboration.
Working in Sprints as a part of a self-organizing team, contributing to the evolution of our products.
Maintain previous released software.

